John Moulton                                









Curiosity. Humility. Leadership.
Meet Our Executive Leadership






















Jeff Stafeil
Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer









                                        As Adient’s executive vice president and chief financial officer, Jeff leads all of our financial activities, including treasury, tax and audit.

Over the course of his career, Jeff has developed extensive operational leadership and financial management experience, primarily within automotive supplier companies, private equity firms and business consultant agencies. He comes to Adient from Visteon, a global automotive electronics supplier and Fortune 500 company. There, he served as executive vice president and chief financial officer.

Prior to working at Visteon, Jeff held a series of domestic and international executive finance roles within the automotive sector. He also held management positions at Booz Allen Hamilton, Peterson Consulting and Ernst & Young.

Jeff is a member of the board of trustees for the Autism Alliance of Michigan. He previously served on the board of directors and as the audit committee chairman of Mentor Graphics and Metaldyne Performance Group. 

Jeff holds a Master of Business Administration from Duke University’s Fuqua School of Business, as well as a Bachelor of Science in accounting from Indiana University.
                                    

























    
