Executive Profile
Jeffrey M. Stafeil  Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President, Adient plcAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 8 different industries.47$1,463,444As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Jeffrey M. Stafeil, also known as Jeff, has been Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President at Adient plc since April 1, 2016. Mr. Stafeil served as Chief Financial Officer of Visteon Corporation since October 31, 2012 until March 31, 2016 and served as its Executive Vice President since November 2, 2012 until March 31, 2016. Mr. Stafeil was a Partner of Heartland Industrial Partners, L.P. and Heartland Industrial Partners I, L.P. He served as the Chief ... Financial Officer and Executive Vice President of DURA Automotive Systems, LLC (alternate name, Dura Automotive Systems Inc.) from December 2008 to 2010 and served as its Chief Executive Officer from October 2010 to 2012. Mr. Stafeil served as a Special Advisor of Asahi Tec Corporation. Prior to joining DURA, he served as the Chief Financial Officer and Member of Management Board of Klöckner Pentaplast Europe GmbH & Co. KG (alternate name, Klöckner Pentaplast GmbH & Co. KG). He served as Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President of Oldco M Corporation (also known as, Metaldyne Corp.) from 2001 to April 2, 2007. He also served as Chief Accounting Officer of Oldco M Corporation until March 27, 2007 and its Vice President and Corporate Controller from February 2001 to July 2003. He was responsible for all corporate financial activities. In addition, he also assumes a senior role at RHJ International (RHJI). Since joining Metaldyne in 2001, Mr. Stafeil led the Investor Relations function, providing a clear and credible voice to Metaldyne's investors during a period of challenging financial markets. He served as Executive Vice President of Metaldyne Company. Prior to Metaldyne, he served as Senior Managing Director of Heartland Industrial Partners from 1992 to November 2005, where he led the effort to create a new Metaldyne financial culture and also held various positions with Mobil Corporation, Peterson Consulting and Ernst & Young. He was a Consultant at Booz, Allen & Hamilton from July 1998 to 2000. Among other activities while in this role, Mr. Stafeil led the shared services implementation across a multinational petroleum company. He served as a Director of Metaldyne Performance Group Inc. since August 2014 until April 06, 2017. He served as a Director of Mentor Graphics Corporation since 2014 until March 30, 2017. He served as a Director of DURA Automotive Systems, LLC from June 27, 2008 to October 2012 and Meridian Corporation from 2006 to 2009. From 2009 to 2012, he served as a Director of J.L. French Automotive Castings Inc. From 2006 to 2009, he served as a Director of Meridian Automotive Systems. He served as a Director of Hanon Systems Corp. since November 20, 2012. He served as a Board Member of Klöckner Pentaplast Europe GmbH & Co. KG. He served as a Director of Oldco M Corporation from February 2007 to April 2, 2007. He served as a Director of HHI. He holds CPA accreditation. Mr. Stafeil holds a Bachelor of Science in Accounting from Indiana University and an Master of Business Administration from Fuqua School of Business Duke University.Read Full Background




